{"title_page": "List of Canadian supercentenarians", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\nThis article lists [[Canadians|Canadian]] [[supercentenarian]]s (people from [[Canada]] who have attained the age of at least 110 years).<ref name=\"GRG\">{{cite web | access-date=2019-09-18 | url=http://grg.org/SC/WorldSCRankingsList.html | title=GRG World Supercentenarian Rankings List | website=Gerontology Research Group}}</ref> The oldest verified Canadian person ever was [[Marie-Louise Meilleur]], who died in 1998 aged 117 years, 230 days.\n\n== Oldest Canadian people ever ==\n{{legend2|#F9F9F9|Deceased|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#99FF99|Living|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Rank\n! Name\n! Sex\n! data-sort-type=\"date\" | Birth date\n! data-sort-type=\"date\" | Death date\n! Age\n! Birthplace\n! Place of death <br /> or residence\n\n|-\n|{{0}}1\n|[[Marie-Louise Meilleur]]<ref name=\"Supercentenarians who lived in Canada\">{{cite web | url=http://www.grg.org/Adams/L/Canada.HTM | title=Verified Supercentenarian Cases Canada (as of Mar. 25, 2007) | accessdate=2019-09-18 | website=www.grg.org}}</ref>\n|align=center|F\n|29 August 1880\n|16 April 1998\n|117 years, 230 days\n|[[Quebec]]\n|[[Ontario]]\n\n|-\n|{{0}}2\n|Mary Ann Rhodes<ref name=\"World's Oldest People in 1999\">{{cite web | url=http://grg.org/Adams/1999WOPeople.htm | title=Validated Supercentenarian Cases (as of Jan. 1, 1999) | accessdate=2019-09-18 | website=www.grg.org}}</ref>\n|align=center|F\n|12 August 1882\n|3 March 1998\n|nowrap|115 years, 203 days\n|Ontario\n|Ontario\n|-\n|{{0}}3\n|Julie Winnefred Bertrand<ref name=\"Supercentenarians who lived in Canada\" />\n|align=center|F\n|16 September 1891\n|18 January 2007\n|115 years, 124 days\n|Quebec\n|Quebec\n\n|-\n|{{0}}4\n|Mary Josephine Ray<ref name=\"GRG\" />\n|align=center|F\n|17 May 1895\n|7 March 2010\n|114 years, 294 days\n|[[Prince Edward Island]]\n|[[United States]]\n\n|-\n|{{0}}5\n|Ellen