anitoba\n|Manitoba\n\n|-\n|86\n|Mary Sloan<ref name=\"GRG Deaths in 2008\" />\n|align=center|F\n|11 June 1898\n|12 August 2008\n|110 years, 62 days\n|Ontario\n|Ontario\n\n|-\n|87\n|Irene Nadeau<ref name=\"GRG Deaths in 2007\" />\n|align=center|F\n|25 April 1897\n|9 June 2007\n|110 years, 45 days\n|Quebec\n|United States\n\n|-\n|88\n|Laura Rollock<ref name=\"Supercentenarians who lived in Canada\" />\n|align=center|F\n|16 November 1878\n|29 December 1988\n|110 years, 43 days\n|Nova Scotia\n|Nova Scotia\n\n|-\n|89\n|Emma Welz<ref name=\"GRG Table B2\">{{cite web | url=http://grg.org/Adams/B2.HTM | title=Table B, as of March 21, 2012 | accessdate=5 December 2018 | website=grg.org}}</ref>\n|align=center|F\n|16 June 1884\n|21 July 1994\n|110 years, 35 days\n|Ontario\n|Ontario\n\n|-\n|90\n|Chester Pushie<ref name=\"Supercentenarians who lived in Canada\" />\n|align=center|M\n|24 June 1884\n|22 July 1994\n|110 years, 28 days\n|Nova Scotia\n|Nova Scotia\n\n|-\n|91\n|Joseph Saint-Amour<ref name=\"Supercentenarians who lived in Canada\" />\n|align=center|M\n|26 February 1852\n|16 March 1962\n|110 years, 18 days\n|Quebec{{efn|name=Quebec}}\n|Quebec\n\n|-\n|92\n|Rose McDonald<ref name=\"Supercentenarians who lived in Canada\" />\n|align=center|F\n|5 September 1890\n|16 September 2000\n|110 years, 11 days\n|Nova Scotia\n|Nova Scotia \n|}\n\n{{notelist}}\n\n== Biographies ==\n\n=== Sum Ying Fung ===\n'''Sum Ying Fung''' (n\u00e9e '''Eng''', {{zh|s=\u5434\u5982\u82f1}}, 27 January 1899 \u2013 6 December 2011), was an [[Asian Canadian]] [[supercentenarian]] who was the oldest person in Canada in 2011.\n\nSum Ying Eng was born in Wing On Village, [[Enping|Yanping]], [[China]] in 1899.<ref name=\"report\">{{cite web | url=https://theprovince.com/news/Oldest+Canadian+Ying+Fung+dies+peacefully+Burnaby/5854257/story.html | title=Oldest Canadian Sum Ying Fung dies peacefully in Burnaby | date=2010-12-19 | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120108012406/http://www.theprovince.com/news/Oldest+Canadian+Ying+Fung+dies+peacefully+Burnaby/5854257/story.html | archivedate=January 8, 2012}}</ref> In 1926, she married Chong Lim Fung, who had been working in Canada since 1911. Chong Lim would travel to visit Sum Ying regularly in the ensuing years and they had three children.<ref name=\":0\" /> However, the [[Chinese Immigration Act, 1923|Chinese Exclusion Act]] prevented her from joining her husband in Canada. In 1954, she emigrated to Canada under the sponsorship of her husband.<ref name=\":1\">{{cite web | url=http://www.iask.ca/news/canada/2011/1214/106947.html | title=\u52a0\u62ff\u5927\u6700\u957f\u5bff\u4eba\u745e 112\u5c81\u534e\u88d4\u5434\u5982\u82f1\u5351\u8bd7\u7701\u8f9e\u4e16 | date=2011-12-14 | accessdate=2015-11-17 | language=Chinese | website=\u52a0\u62ff\u5927\u5bb6\u56ed}}</ref> The couple settled in [[Chinatown, Vancouver]] that year. The Fung family moved to [[East Vancouver]] upon Chong Lim's death in 1967.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nIn 1989, she developed a brain tumour, underwent surgery, and survived. She visited China later that year and was in [[Beijing]] during the military crackdown of [[Tiananmen Square protests of 1989|Tiananmen Square protests]]. She and her family fled Beijing among a group of German tourists.<ref name=vancouversun-20111213 />\n\nIn January 2011, Sum Ying Fung became the oldest person in Canada, after the death of Elizabeth Buhler.<ref>{{cite news | access-date=2015-11-17 | url=http://thevancouversun.tumblr.com/post/2965444296/when-she-was-born-queen-victoria-ruled-england | title=112-year-old Vancouver woman may be oldest Canadian | date=2011-01-28 | last=Pynn | first=Larry | last2=Sherlock | first2=Tracy | newspaper=[[Vancouver Sun]]}}</ref> The Queen congratulated Fung in a letter on her 112th birthday on 27 January 2011 and the Mayor of Vancouver declared that day \"Fung Eng Sum Ying Day\".<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":0\" />\n\nFung died of natural causes at the claimed age of 112, at [[Burnaby General Hospital]] in British Columbia on 6 December 2011. At the time of her death she was survived by two of her three children, 14 grandchildren, 25 great-grand children, and 2 great-great-grand children.<ref name=\"vancouversun-20111213\">{{cite news | access-date=5 December 2015 | archive-date=8 January 2012 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120108142453/https://vancouversun.com/life/Vancouver+Ying+Fung+Canada+oldest+resident+dies/5856080/story.html | url-status=dead | url=https://vancouversun.com/life/Vancouver+Ying+Fung+Canada+oldest+resident+dies/5856080/story.html | title=Vancouver's Sum Ying Fung, Canada's oldest resident, dies at the age of 112 | date=13 December 2011 | last=Woo | first=Andrea | newspaper=[[The Vancouver Sun]]}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{cite web | url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/story/2011/12/13/bc-oldest-woman-dies.html?cmp=rss | title=Woman who was oldest living Canadian dies at 112 \u2013 British Columbia \u2013 CBC News | publisher=Cbc.ca | date=2011-12-13 | accessdate=2011-12-15}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{portalbar|Biography|Canada}}\n{{Longevity}}\n\n[[Category:Canadian supercentenarians| ]]\n[[Category:Lists of supercentenarians by nationality|Canadian]]\n[[Category:Lists of Canadian people|Supercentenarians]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\nThis article lists [[Canadians|Canadian]] [[supercentenarian]]s (people from [[Canada]] who have attained the age of at least 110 years).<ref name=\"GRG\">{{cite web | access-date=2019-09-18 | url=http://grg.org/SC/WorldSCRankingsList.html | title=GRG World Supercentenarian Rankings List | website=Gerontology Research Group}}</ref> The oldest verified Canadian person ever was [[Marie-Louise Meilleur]], who died in 1998 aged 117 years, 230 days.\n\n== Oldest Canadian people ever ==\n{{legend2|#F9F9F9|Deceased|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#99FF99|Living|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\